ended to the dead; on the third day he rose again from the dead; he ascended into Heaven, and is seated at the right hand of God the Father Almighty; from there he will come to judge the living and the dead. I believe in the Holy Spirit, the holy Catholic Church, the Communion of Saints, the forgiveness of sins, the resurrection of the body, and life everlasting. Amen. Using the Rosary beads, on the Our Father Beads say the following: Eternal Father, I offer Thee the Body and Blood, Soul and Divinity of Thy dearly beloved Son, Our Lord Jesus Christ, in atonement for our sins and those of the whole world. After each Eternal Father prayer, on the ten Hail Mary Beads say the following: For the sake of His sorrowful Passion, have mercy on us and on the whole world. (Repeat step 4 and 5 for all five decades). Conclude with the Holy God prayer, repeated three times: Holy God, Holy Mighty One, Holy Immortal One, have mercy on us and on the whole world. Pray the Optional Closing Prayers Eternal God, in whom mercy is endless and the treasury of compassion ‚Äî inexhaustible, look kindly upon us and increase Your mercy in us, that in difficult moments we might not despair nor become despondent, but with great confidence submit ourselves to Your holy will, which is Love and Mercy itself. O Greatly Merciful God, Infinite Goodness, today all mankind calls out from the abyss of its misery to Your mercy ‚Äî to Your compassion, O God; and it is with its mighty voice of misery that it cries out. Gracious God, do not reject the prayer of this earth‚Äôs exiles! O Lord, Goodness beyond our understanding, Who are acquainted with our misery through and through, and know that by our own power we cannot ascend to You, we implore You: anticipate us with Your grace and keep on increasing Your mercy in us, that we may faithfully do Your holy will all through our life and at death‚Äôs hour. Let the omnipotence of Your mercy shield us from the darts of our salvation‚Äôs enemies, that we may with confidence, as Your children, await Your [Son‚Äôs] final coming ‚Äî that day known to You alone. And we expect to obtain everything promised us by Jesus in spite of all our wretchedness. For Jesus is our Hope: through His merciful Heart, as through an open gate, we pass through to heaven (Diary, 1570).

In the name of the Father, and of the Son, and of the Holy Spirit. Amen.



